{'chapter_title': 'Bhagavad Gita: Chapter 18, Verse 32', 'sanskrit': ['अधर्मं धर्ममिति या मन्यते तमसावृता |', 'सर्वार्थान्विपरीतांश्च बुद्धि: सा पार्थ तामसी || 32||'], 'latin': ['adharmaṁ dharmam iti yā manyate tamasāvṛitā', 'sarvārthān viparītānśh cha buddhiḥ sā pārtha tāmasī'], 'translation': ['\r\n                            ', '\r\n                            That intellect which is shrouded in darkness, imagining irreligion to be religion, and perceiving untruth to be the truth, is of the nature of ignorance.\r\n                        ']}